snippet.textDisplay:
There are better games so far. Kingdom Come: Deliverance 2 is already GOTY for anyone who’s played it, and I’m saying that both objectively and subjectively. Schedule 1 is a small indie game, but it’s somehow better than most AAA titles coming out. Ena: Dream BBQ is another solid indie, and it’s free. There are plenty of Souls-likes now, along with other games that just do it better.

And this year is packed with insane releases. Ghost of Yotei, DOOM 3, GTA 6, Metroid Prime 4, a new 3D Mario (not announced, but almost guaranteed for Switch 2), Phantom Blade Zero, Borderlands 4, Elden Ring and Lies of P DLC, Death Stranding 2, Ninja Gaiden 4, John Carpenter’s Toxic Commando (could go either way), Wolf Among Us 2, Subnautica 2, Snake Eater remake—the list goes on.

That said, AC Shadows is actually great if you put in the time. It’s not just about the opening few hours. If you actually explore and take on the quests, there’s a lot there. Charlie just rushed through it and didn’t even unlock the main samurai character. Steam reviews and PlayStation Store ratings back that up, so I know I’m not the only one who thinks the game is good. It’s not an amazing game, but it’s still great, and the world is really well-crafted. So yeah, Berzerker it’s a cool game, but if you care about getting the most out of your time and money, it might be worth waiting to see what else drops.
